summary:
I am a social science and development graduate interested in poverty analysis and anti-poverty policies such as social protection. My 15 years of professional activities have combined socioeconomic research and evaluation; development project design, implementation, and experimentation; and training design, management, and facilitation. My research and action research have covered aspects of poverty, child poverty, child rights, social protection, cooperatives, rural development, social inclusion, etc. 

Expertise:
•	Quantitative and qualitative research and evaluation including design and implementation of household surveys such as baseline, mid-term and end-line studies;
•	Policy analysis, implementation, and reform; 
•	Designing of training courses, administration, and management of training courses; 
•	Development project design and implementation; 

Researched for: Government of Bangladesh, UNDP, UNICEF, UNFPA, Oxfam, NRECA, FAO, ILO, CARE, Oxford Policy Management (OPM), Save the Children
Worked for: The United Nations, The Government of Bangladesh, and the Private Sector
